title: Congratulating Carolyn E. Garski upon the occasion of receiving the Girl Scout Gold Award, the most prestigious honor a Girl Scout can earn
fulltext:
LEGISLATIVE  RESOLUTION  congratulating Carolyn E. Garski upon the occa-
sion of receiving the Girl Scout Gold Award, the most prestigious  honor
a Girl Scout can earn

WHEREAS,  Carolyn  E.  Garski of Macedon, New York, will be honored with
the Girl Scout Gold Award, the highest award and Girl Scouting's highest
achievement, at the Young Women of Distinction Event to be held  in  the
Spring of 2011; and
  WHEREAS, Girl Scouting has cultivated in our Nation's young people the
goals of building solid values of sisterhood and the importance of work-
ing  with  others, stimulating both mind and body, instilling pride, and
encouraging community service and success; and
  WHEREAS, Girl Scouting has expanded  the  horizons  of  the  countless
hundreds  of  thousands who have participated in Scouting programs which
have made Scouting an American and international institution; and
  WHEREAS, Carolyn E. Garski completed many activities, including a Gold
Award  community  service  project  which  she  planned,  developed  and
executed; and
  WHEREAS,  For  her  project,  Carolyn  E. Garski held an online safety
seminar for teens and parents which included tips for online protection;
and
  WHEREAS, The Gold Award symbolizes outstanding accomplishments in  the
areas  of  leadership,  community  service, career planning and personal
development; it is tangible evidence of Carolyn E. Garski's high charac-
ter and commitment, and is a harbinger of  her  future  service  to  her
community, New York State and our Nation; now, therefore, be it
  RESOLVED,  That  this  Legislative Body pause in its deliberations, in
recognition of Carolyn E. Garski's achievement in earning the Girl Scout
Gold Award and wishing her success, health  and  happiness;  and  be  it
further
  RESOLVED, That a copy of this Resolution, suitably engrossed, be tran-
smitted to Carolyn E. Garski, Macedon, New York.
